  <p>A couple quick things to point out here. The first is that we use multiplication as it allows us to "accelerate" our progress as we gain confidence. Another is that we can look at the same ballot more than once. This is pretty counterintuitive! Why would we need to verify something if weâ€™ve already manually double-checked it? The answer is that we want to treat every ballot the exact same. Removing some ballots means it gets slightly more likely that we pick a new ballot each time, which could bias our results.</p>


